and thorax traumas (39%), this was of enormous assistance in the differential 
diagnosis. Level and rate of increase of oxygen saturation can be an indication 
of the severity of a thorax trauma. The limitations of pulse oximetric 
monitoring, especially those resulting from low peripheral perfusion in trauma 
cases (7 patients), are fairly rare.

